.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-5-4::.
The people use 6 different means of transport: bike, airplane, quad-bike, car, skateboard, subway
6 different games are played: chess, canasta, scrabble, mah-jongg, monopoly, domino
 1. the person playing mah-jongg is somewhere to the right of the person driving the airplane##5
 2. the person driving the quad-bike is on the left or right of the person driving the subway##3
 3. the person driving the skateboard is on the right of the person playing mah-jongg##1
 4. the person playing canasta is the person driving the bike##1
 5. the person playing monopoly is on the far left or far right##3
 6. the person driving the airplane is somewhere to the left of the person driving the subway##5
 7. the person playing canasta is somewhere to the left of the person driving the quad-bike##5
 8. the person driving the bike is on the far left##1
 9. the person playing scrabble is on the left or right of the person playing domino##3
10. the person playing domino is somewhere to the left of the person playing scrabble##5
11. the person driving the car is in an odd position##4
12. the person playing chess is on the right of the person playing scrabble##1
13. the person driving the quad-bike is on the right of the person driving the airplane##1

.:: Answer ::.
|            |    1    |    2     |   3    |    4    |       5       |    6     |
| Transport   | bike     | airplane     | quad-bike  | subway     | car | skateboard |
| Game       | canasta | domino | scrabble | chess | mah-jongg          | monopoly   |

